description:
Recently sold: $197,500. This lovely Hastings twinhome is equipped with 4 beds, 2 baths, 2 car garage & over 1,700 Sq.Ft. This charming home is situated with a private wooded backyard.
As you enter the foyer you are greeted with bright, natural light & beaming floors that flow up the step and thru the main level.  The kitchen features all white appliances & opens to a quaint dining room. The open floor plan allows this setting to be the perfect place for entertaining your family and friends.  You will find 2 large bedrooms with ample closet space & a full bathroom.
Moving to the the lower level you will find another large entertainment space that walks out to your private, fenced-in backyard, perfect if you have pets.  The large patio is great for hosting summertime BBQ's.
You will find 2 additional bedrooms, a full bathroom, laundry & an extra room for storage. Located near Hwy 61 - near shops & parks, this twinhome checks off all the boxes. You will not want to miss out! 2019-08-19

description: Recently sold: $202,000.

Recently sold: $250,000. Quaint old farm house. A new (2010) three season porch (7 x 18 ft) and 17 x 22 ft bedroom/family room addition added to the front of the house. A cedar deck added (2009) off the east side with a single french door access from the dining room which is now a work-out room. The deck wraps around connects to the three season porch and new addition. The property has several out buildings; a large pole barn, a shop, two detached garages and a separate fenced dog yard off the shop with indoor/outdoor roofed dog kennels. The shop and small garage were re-roofed with steel summer 2009. The house was reroofed summer 2010. The downstairs bathroom was redone and has a single whirlpool tube. The plumbing was redone and the hot water heater replaced and a new pressure tank done over 2007-2009. The kitchen and pantry also updated summer 2009. The upstair bedrooms have the original pine floors and the kitchen has the original maple floor, all have been refinished. The living room and dining room have floating cork linoleum. The new bedroom addition on the front has a vaulted knotty pine ceiling and has an attached 3 season porch with knotty pine walls and ceiling. The 3 season room has a ceiling fan that heats as well as cools. All the windows were replaced with double hung windows summer 2010. The attic was reinsulated Fall 2010.
